<font size="+2"></font><p align="left"><font size="+2"><b><u>Tentative List of Informal Discussions and Lecture Topics</u></b></font></p>

The motivation for both lecture topics and hands-on exercises is <b><i>operational</i></b>, i.e., 
the use of concepts in performing calculations and the emphasis of the <b><i>intersection</i></b> of theory, experiment, and calculation.
<br>
<br>
<b><u>Overview of Computational Chemistry Applications</u></b>
<ul>
<!--
<li><a href="http://homepages.uconn.edu/rossi/chem5326/files/cc_for_inorganic_chemistsp_4up.pdf">Lecture</a>
-->
</ul>
<b><u>Electronic Structure Calculations</u></b>
<ul> 
<li>Symmetry Concepts and Group Theory
<li>Hartree-Fock and Density Functional Methods
<li>Reaction Pathways and Transition States
<li>Spectroscopy of Organic and Transition Metal Compounds
